@page "/"
<PageTitle>Blazor Demo • Overview</PageTitle>

<section class="hero">
    <div class="container-narrow">
        <span class="badge-soft">.NET 8 • Blazor WebAssembly</span>
        <h1 class="mt-3">Blazor, explained clearly—then shown.</h1>
        <p class="lead" style="color:#c6cad6">
            A concise intro for first-time readers, a runnable example, and a short tutorial
            your classmates can complete in under an hour.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-3 d-flex gap-2">
            <a class="btn btn-brand" href="/slides">View Slides</a>
            <a class="btn btn-outline-light" href="/tutorial">Do the Tutorial</a>
            <a class="btn btn-outline-light" href="/references">References & Cheat Sheet</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<div class="container-narrow" style="margin-top:2rem">
    <div class="card">
        <h3>What is Blazor?</h3>
        <p>
            Blazor lets you build interactive client-side UIs with C# and Razor components, running on WebAssembly.
            You write .NET end-to-end, share models, and avoid JS for most app logic.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h3>Where it fits in a system</h3>
        <p>
            Typical stack: <strong>Blazor WASM</strong> (UI) ⇄ <strong>Minimal API / ASP.NET Core</strong> (services) ⇄
            <strong>DB (SQL/NoSQL)</strong> + Auth (Identity/Entra/Magic Link).
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h3>Pros & Cons (at a glance)</h3>
        <ul class="mb-0">
            <li><strong>+ C# all the way down</strong> for teams already in .NET</li>
            <li><strong>+ Reusable components</strong>, strong tooling, type safety</li>
            <li><strong>– Initial payload</strong> (WASM) can be larger</li>
            <li><strong>– JS ecosystem parity</strong> sometimes requires interop</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h3>Try a live example</h3>
        <p>Open <a href="/counter">Counter</a> to see event handling, two-way binding, and basic validation.</p>
    </div>
</div>